{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b33786b4-9ed4-4a87-82f4-29545b04161f","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n**1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)**\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` handles all package references, `using` directives, and test runner config automatically.\n\n**2. Enable parallel execution (assembly-level)**\n\nAdd to any file (or a dedicated `AssemblyInfo.cs`):\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n`MethodLevel` = max parallelism (methods across classes). Use `ClassLevel` if you want classes to run in parallel but methods within a class to be sequential.\n\n**3. Opt out for database tests**\n\nDecorate your sequential test classes with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Should_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Should_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `[DoNotParallelize]` makes that class wait until all parallel tests finish, then runs its methods sequentially\n- You can also apply `[DoNotParallelize]` to individual `[TestMethod]`s if only some methods need it\n- To limit parallelism (e.g., 4 threads), use: `[assembly: Parallelize(Workers = 4, Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a20b1c59-8f0e-4eb0-bc9a-0916628ba992","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up a new MSTest project using MSTest.Sdk with parallel test execution by default, but with sequential execution for database integration tests. Let me provide the recommended setup.\n\nLet me think about what I know about MSTest.Sdk and parallel execution:\n\n1. **MSTest.Sdk** - This is the simplified SDK-style project format for MSTest. Instead of referencing individual packages, you use `<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/...\">`.\n\n2. **Parallel execution** - MSTest supports parallel execution via assembly-level attributes or `.runsettings`.\n\n3. **Sequential for specific tests** - You can use `[DoNotParallelize]` attribute on specific test classes.\n\n\nI'll set up the project file with MSTest.Sdk and configure the assembly-level parallelization, then show how to mark database tests for sequential execution. I should provide clear guidance on the MSTest configuration and parallel execution setup.","outputTokens":950,"requestId":"A02E:1007E7:63C1D79:6C54AE8:6A034D6A"},"id":"751304c8-6c9d-410c-9b01-5162ccadae8c","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:55:48.905Z","parentId":"11bb953d-4517-4dcc-814b-175ecc7cf990"}
